               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jāmiʿ-i ʿAbbāsī by Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ʿĀmilī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104963 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85121424" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_144C-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1167">Jāmiʿ-i ʿAbbāsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1167">جامع عبّاسى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Extensive treatise on Twelver Shīʿī jurisprudence by 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656953.0x000001 viaf_27052262" role="aut">Shaykh Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ʿĀmilī</persName>(d. 1030/1621), dedicated to 
                <persName key="viaf_77109363" role="dte">Shāh ʿAbbās Ṣafavī I</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work, consisting of twenty chapters termed bāb, is the extended version completed by 
                <persName key="person_f3204" role="ctb">Niẓām ibn Ḥusayn Sāvajī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 103r): copied from a copy owned by Mukhliṣ Ḥasan Khān ṣāḥib at the maqām or location of Sivāʾī Jaypūr, in 
                <placeName>Nohara (Sukhdeopura village)</placeName>of Rājah Har Sahāy, written by Mīr Fakhr al-Dīn ʿAlī, Friday morning, 24 Z̲ī Ḥijjah RY 13 of Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam, 1188/25 February 1775.
                        </p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_27052262">Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ʿĀmilī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_27052262">بهاء الدّين محمّد عاملى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
